# .cursorrules — WordPress ACF Theme Development

## Design Source of Truth
- Reference the design artifact at https://claude.ai/code/artifact/1c02bcb5-f44b-4b70-8d6d-687c17e185c6?org=41ad3a15-ecd2-4a86-b036-ce0d96dba095 for all visual/structural decisions
- Extracted design folder here - @wp-content/themes/design
- Compare rendered blocks against the design for spacing, colour, typography, responsive behaviour
- Flag any design ambiguities before building (don't guess)

---

## CRITICAL: Build One Block Per Session

### Workflow (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
1. Build ONE block only (ACF registration + template + SCSS + JS if needed)
2. STOP and wait for explicit approval from human
3. Wait for human to:
   - Review the code
   - Test in WordPress admin
   - Verify on mobile/tablet/desktop
   - Confirm the design matches
4. Only after human says "build next" proceed to the next block

### Never Do This
- ❌ Build multiple blocks in one response
- ❌ Assume all blocks follow the same pattern without testing
- ❌ Skip testing/review cycle
- ❌ Auto-commit without human review

**Do NOT proceed to the next block until human explicitly says "build [next block name]"**

---

## ACF Block Architecture

- All blocks are flexible content blocks

---

## PHP Standards & Security

### File Headers
Every PHP file must start with:
```php
<?php
declare(strict_types=1);

/**
 * Block: [Block Name]
 * Description of what this block does
 */
```

### Inside Block Templates
- ONLY use `get_sub_field()` inside flexible content loops — NEVER `get_field()`
- Always escape output:
  - Text/HTML: `esc_html()` or `wp_kses_post()`
  - URLs: `esc_url()`
  - Attributes: `esc_attr()`
  - Data attributes: `wp_json_encode()` then `esc_attr()`
- Example:
```php
  <?php
  $heading = get_sub_field('heading');
  $image = get_sub_field('background_image');
  ?>
  <section class="block block--hero">
    <h1 class="block__heading"><?php echo esc_html($heading); ?></h1>
    <img 
      src="<?php echo esc_url($image['url']); ?>" 
      alt="<?php echo esc_attr($image['alt']); ?>"
      class="block__image"
    />
  </section>
```

### Forbidden Actions — STOP & ASK
- Do NOT modify `wp-config.php`, `.htaccess` without explicit approval
- Do NOT create custom post types, taxonomies, or metaboxes
- Do NOT install new plugins
- Do NOT modify git remote URLs or commit version numbers automatically
- Do NOT add inline styles (use CSS classes only)
- Do NOT use `eval()`, `extract()`, or variable variables

---

## JavaScript Standards

### File Structure
- Block-specific JS: `assets/js/blocks/[block-name].js`
- Shared utilities: `assets/js/lib/[utility-name].js`
- Main entry point: `assets/js/main.js` (imports and initializes all blocks)
- Enqueue block JS via ACF `enqueue_assets` callback (same as CSS)

### Vanilla JS Only
- NO jQuery, NO frameworks, NO build tools beyond SCSS
- Use native DOM APIs: `querySelector`, `addEventListener`, `classList`
- ES6+ syntax OK (const, let, arrow functions, destructuring)
- Avoid polyfills for modern browsers

---

## SCSS/CSS Standards

### Structure
- Design tokens in `_variables.scss`
- Colours in `_colors.scss` (reference these ONLY)
- Block styles in `assets/scss/components/`

### BEM Naming
- Block: `.block`, `.block--[name]` (e.g., `.block--hero-section`)
- Element: `.block__[element]` (e.g., `.block__heading`, `.block__image`)
- Modifier: `.block--[modifier]` (e.g., `.block--hero-section--dark`)
- NO utility classes, NO nested selectors deeper than 2 levels
- Example:
```scss
  .block--hero-section {
    padding: var(--spacing-lg);
    background-color: var(--color-primary);

    &__heading {
      font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
      color: var(--color-text-light);
    }

    &__image {
      width: 100%;
      object-fit: cover;
    }
  }
```

### Responsive Breakpoints
- Use SCSS variables only: `@media (max-width: var(--breakpoint-tablet))`
- Breakpoints defined in `_variables.scss`:
  - `--breakpoint-mobile`: 576px
  - `--breakpoint-tablet`: 768px
  - `--breakpoint-desktop`: 1024px
  - `--breakpoint-wide`: 1440px
- Mobile-first: base styles are mobile, add `@media` for larger screens
- Never hardcode pixel values for spacing/font-size — use CSS variables

---

## Block Development Workflow

### Before Building
- Look at design artifact and desing folder (assets are also there) for the component

### Template Build Steps
1. Write ACF fields
2. Create block template
3. Create SCSS file
4. Add SCSS import to style.scss
5. Register enqueue callback for block-specific assets
6. Test in WordPress admin - https://localhost/sweetmunchies_wordpresscms/ (create page - if not existing, add the block, fill fields)
7. Verify on mobile, tablet, desktop breakpoints
8. Compare rendered output to design artifact

### Field Group Registration Checklist
- [ ] Block name in kebab-case
- [ ] ACF field group created with correct location rule
- [ ] All fields have clear labels and help text
- [ ] Field names match design intent (e.g., if design shows "CTA Button", field is `cta_link`)
- [ ] Required fields marked appropriately
- [ ] Repeater fields have min/max counts (if applicable)
- [ ] Flexible content layout slug matches block name

### Template Checklist
- [ ] get_sub_field() used ONLY (never get_field())
- [ ] All text output escaped (esc_html, esc_url, etc.)
- [ ] CSS classes follow BEM strictly
- [ ] No inline styles
- [ ] No hardcoded colours/spacing (use CSS variables)
- [ ] Responsive attributes set (e.g., width, height, srcset)
- [ ] Images have alt text (pulled from ACF image field)
- [ ] No console errors when rendered

### SCSS Checklist
- [ ] Uses only colours from _colors.scss
- [ ] Uses only spacing from _variables.scss
- [ ] Responsive breakpoints use @media (max-width: var(--breakpoint-X))
- [ ] Mobile-first approach (base styles first, media queries for larger screens)
- [ ] BEM naming followed strictly
- [ ] Max nesting depth: 2 levels
- [ ] All selectors namespaced under .block--[name]

---

## Common Mistakes — PREVENTION MODE

### Mistake: Using get_field() inside flexible content loop
**WRONG:**
```php
<?php
while (have_rows('page_content')) : the_row();
  $heading = get_field('heading'); // ❌ WRONG
endwhile;
?>
```
**RIGHT:**
```php
<?php
while (have_rows('page_content')) : the_row();
  $heading = get_sub_field('heading'); // ✅ CORRECT
endwhile;
?>
```

### Mistake: Hardcoding colours or spacing
**WRONG:**
```scss
.block--hero {
  padding: 32px 16px; // ❌ Hardcoded
  background-color: #0066cc; // ❌ Hardcoded
}
```
**RIGHT:**
```scss
.block--hero {
  padding: var(--spacing-lg) var(--spacing-sm);
  background-color: var(--color-primary);
}
```

### Mistake: Forgetting to escape output
**WRONG:**
```php
<h1><?php echo $heading; ?></h1> <!-- ❌ XSS vulnerability -->
```
**RIGHT:**
```php
<h1><?php echo esc_html($heading); ?></h1>
```

### Mistake: Deep nesting in SCSS
**WRONG:**
```scss
.block--hero {
  .container {
    .row {
      .col {
        padding: 1rem; // ❌ 4 levels deep
      }
    }
  }
}
```
**RIGHT:**
```scss
.block--hero {
  padding: var(--spacing-md);

  &__content {
    padding: var(--spacing-md); // ✅ Max 2 levels
  }
}
```

---

## Git Commits

- One block per commit
- Commit message format: `feat(blocks): Add [block-name] block with ACF fields`
- Include both PHP and SCSS changes in same commit
- Never auto-bump version numbers
- Never push I will do it myself

---

## Success Criteria

A block is "done" when:
- ✅ ACF field group is registered and editable
- ✅ Block template renders without errors
- ✅ Output matches design artifact (spacing, colours, typography)
- ✅ Responsive on mobile (576px), tablet (768px), desktop (1024px+)
- ✅ All text escaped, no inline styles, no console errors
- ✅ Reference block pattern followed (ACF registration, template structure, SCSS organization)
- ✅ Code reviewed by human (you)
- ✅ Committed with clear message